================================================================================
PATCH: Slim/Web/Settings/Server/Status.pm
================================================================================
Description:
  Extends Status.pm to extract and pass the internet access section
  to the web template for display on the server status page.

Changes:
  - Adds extraction of 'internetaccess' provider data
  - Uses _extractGroup() to extract INFORMATION_MENU_INTERNET_ACCESS
  - Position: after 'server', before 'perl' (consistent with SystemInfo.pm)
  - Makes internetaccess.items available to the template

Technical Details:
  - The _extractGroup() function searches the menu items array
  - Extracts items matching the INFORMATION_MENU_INTERNET_ACCESS name
  - Creates $paramRef->{internetaccess} for template access
  - Required for web interface display (CLI/Apps work without this)

Flow:
  - SystemInfo.pm → generates menu items
  - Status.pm → extracts and groups items by name
  - status.html → renders grouped items in web interface

Requirements:
  - SystemInfo.pm patch must be applied first
  - strings.txt must contain INFORMATION_MENU_INTERNET_ACCESS
  - status.html template must be patched

Author: Markus Baier
Date: 2025-12-28
================================================================================



--- a/Slim/Web/Settings/Server/Status.pm	2025-12-28 02:29:18.074490056 +0100
+++ b/Slim/Web/Settings/Server/Status.pm	2025-12-28 03:18:46.478117337 +0100
@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@
 	$paramRef->{info} = $paramRef->{info}->{items};
 
 	$paramRef->{server}  = _extractGroup($paramRef, cstring($client, 'INFORMATION_MENU_SERVER'));
+	$paramRef->{internetaccess} = _extractGroup($paramRef, cstring($client, 'INFORMATION_MENU_INTERNET_ACCESS'));
 	$paramRef->{perl}    = _extractGroup($paramRef, cstring($client, 'INFORMATION_MENU_PERL'));
 	$paramRef->{library} = _extractGroup($paramRef, cstring($client, 'INFORMATION_MENU_LIBRARY'));
 	$paramRef->{players} = _extractGroup($paramRef, cstring($client, 'INFORMATION_MENU_PLAYER'));
